  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0bcb\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bbe  \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba8\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bcb\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0b85\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Notification regarding distribution of wheat flour",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Trade, Commerce and Food Security Minister Nalin Fernando has said that a written request will be made to Prima and Serendip companies to distribute the existing stock of wheat flour to the market.",
        "A discussion was held between the minister and wheat flour importers regarding the import of wheat flour.",
        "It has been discussed that there is a shortage of wheat flour in the market due to the limited import of wheat flour.",
        "In that discussion, the Minister of Commerce instructed the Secretary of the Ministry to get a report from the wheat flour importers regarding the production price and capacity of wheat flour.",
        "Due to the current shortage of wheat flour, the price of 50 kg wheat flour has gone up to Rs 20,000. The minister said that the reason for this is the suspension of wheat flour import through India.",
        "Also, Minister Nalin Fernando mentioned that it will take about 2 weeks to bring wheat flour through Turkey. (a)"
      ],
